text:
Hello, Travelers. We'd like to apologize for two errors featured in our official trailer for Genshin Impact V1.6. The errors occur at 3:46‚Äì3:54 and 3:54‚Äì4:00, and are as follows:
1. The event preview for Never-Ending Battle erroneously features the icon for the Crown of Insight among the event rewards.
2. The event preview for Kaboomball Kombat erroneously features the icon for Mystic Enhancement Ore among the event rewards.
We sincerely apologize for any inconvenience caused by these oversights on our part.

text:
Hello,
Idk if this is known issue but I wanted to inform incase you don't know it yet. I noticed if you minimize/alt tab the game when you're launching the game, it causes you to have sometimes (quite often) huge fps drops when you alt tab back in (like not getting above 5fps or so, not measured). Clearing download resources fixes this for next launch so not big issue, but still shouldn't do that. I know this won't be your first priority to fix but please remember to try fix it in some point because I know many people who constantly alt tab or do something on another monitor (like me).

Game Version 1.6.1 Launcher Version 2.9.1.0
PC: Win10, intel i5-8600K + RTX 2080

I don't usually ask for likes, but like this post please so that dev's will see this! 
Thank you!

(or if anyone is on discord server, feel free to copy this there! I couldn't join because it's full.)

text:
The game is about a world that relies on elements (fire,ice,water, electric,nature,wind,earth). People who are favored by the gods are blessed snd gifted a vision, an accessory that lets one wield and manipulate one of the 7 elements. There is a god for each element called Archon, and they oversee one region of the world, which are all based on real countries.

Anemo (Wind)-  Mondstadt, based on Germany.

Geo (Earth)- Liyue, based on China

Electro- Inazuma, based on Japan

Dendro (Nature)- Sumeru, not sure but it's most likely based on Egypt. 

Hydro (Water)- Fontaine, not sure again but I'm thinking either Britain, England or France (like during the 1700s)

Pyro (Fire)- Natlan, not sure where it's based on but it's an indigenous type of region. 

Cryo (Ice)- Snezhnaya, based on Russia

Just because a person is in a certain region does not mean they only get that type of vision (e.g. A person from Mondstadt gets a Pyro Vision) 

It would be best to just see the game for yourself it's also very rich and lore that you won't notice how good it is if you only focus on the story that's showed. 

Although I'd recommend you play Genshin Impact about 2-3 years from now as the game is barely a year old and still has a lot of room to grow.

text:
You little kids need to stop complaining. It takes a lot of work to code, program, test, and execute a game like Genshin Impact. The amount of details that will probably come with Inazuma is insane, and they're trying their best to make sure there is a lot of content because you guys keep complaining on Having nothing to do. Plus, they have to optimize the new regions to make sure mobile players don't have their phones exploding on them from the amount of storage it'll take.

Yes, Genshin Impact most of the time is 75% waiting, but the wait is worth it because the game is beautifully crafted. I just wish you guys would appreciate Mihoyo's hardwork and their vision into making this game, instead of complaining every single damn time. The next time you log onto Genshin, why don't you relax and take in the scenery. Look at the birds and fish in the water, and watch the sun set. Listen to the beautiful music of different places, talk to NPC, read the books you've been collecting, farm better artifacts for your characters, etc. There's a lot of stuff to do, you just gotta look at things differently and stop being greedy. The visuals alone is content that I personally never get bored of. I wish you guys would play Genshin a little less seriously. It's not meant to be rushed. Take your time with things. Let the game PLAY YOU, don't play the game :)

author: Mia Chan MLP

text:
You little kids need to stop complaining. It takes a lot of work to code, program, test, and execute a game like Genshin Impact. The amount of details that will probably come with Inazuma is insane, and they're trying their best to make sure there is a lot of content because you guys keep complaining on Having nothing to do. Plus, they have to optimize the new regions to make sure mobile players don't have their phones exploding on them from the amount of storage it'll take.

Yes, Genshin Impact most of the time is 75% waiting, but the wait is worth it because the game is beautifully crafted. I just wish you guys would appreciate Mihoyo's hardwork and their vision into making this game, instead of complaining every single damn time. The next time you log on Genshin, why don't you relax and take in the scenery. Look at the birds and fish in the water, and watch the sun set. Listen to the beautiful music of different places, talk to NPC, read the books you've been collecting, farm better artifacts for your characters, etc. There's a lot of stuff to do, you just gotta look at things differently and stop being greedy. The visuals alone is content that I personally never get bored of.

author: Mia Chan MLP

text: ¬†@Mia Chan MLP¬† The archipelago isn't a permanent area. Just here for the "Midsummer Event". My feeling (and it's really subjective) about this update is just here to say "Please wait for Inazuma" by offering some beta features in a non permanent area.
author: Alexis Marcon

text: ¬†@Alexis Marcon¬† it doesn't matter if it's not permanent, it's still a whole new area to explore. Seriously, I bet that as soon as Inazuma comes out you'll be the kind of person to explore the whole thing in one day and then ask for Sumeru and get mad when there are other filler updates.
author: Mia Chan MLP

text:
¬†@Mia Chan MLP¬† I just wish the archipelago was a permanent area. I just think it's stupid to unlock a area for a certain time. The devs worked on it so that players could stay there for 6 weeks. For me it's wasted work that could have been invested elsewhere. 
And personally I still haven't finished DragonSpine and I would have liked to be able to go in the Chasm. 
I don't rush the game and explore it at 100% in only 1h. I'd love to take my time and forcing me to explore an area because it's only there for a limited time is really stupid from my point of view.
author: Alexis Marcon

text: ¬†@Alexis Marcon¬† hello? Excuse me? You expect the developers to release a new map or a new region in every updates? All these fillers or so called events are really good for f2p because all these are free primogems. This is really excellent game for f2p. You should appreciate more not complaining... If you just want to watch or play the story. Play it after 10 years üòâ
author: June K

text:
¬†@June K¬† Hello. Of course not I didnt expect a new area for each update. Even in AAA game we dont see that. However, as I said, on my opinion, it's stupid to ask to a team of devs to create a non permanent features, just to give to us, players, some new beta gameplay. 
I prefered to know the archipelago was a permanent feature because it's a real work for some guys in mihoyo. 
In fact it's like the discover of American contient and we say to explorer "Sorry, you can just visit this area between june and july"...
As a players pov, now you know the archipelago exists, but you cant access it forever. What is the justification ? "We are open only for midsummer". It's not logic.

We had a lot of beta feature which are now locked for us, players, and it's sad. 

The F2P argument is invalid second to me because for the first months of launch of Genshin, Miyoho win some millions of dollars... so "because it's a f2p we must be happy and hyped for each update" is ridiculous to think that.

I think, you and the other guys here misunderstand me. I enjoy to know we'll a new update but I'm not hyped because it's non permanent and it's not just a boss or a mini game (like endora or tower defense). I liked these two features and we didnt see it anymore. Same destiny for archipelago.

text: I literally just finished the AR35 Archon Quest ("A New Star Approaches") yesterday, where Zhongli talked about Inazuma, the Electro Archon, and "eternity"; and now I'm watching this trailer speaking of Inazuma, the Electro Archon, and her "eternity" ideology. I can't believe, that's too much of a coincidence! If I had watched this trailer one day earlier, I wouldn't know what Inazuma is, nor about the Electro Archon or her "eternity". And did I get it right? Are they going to continue the next chapter of the Archon quests? If it's so, then watching this trailer now is not just a coincidence, but I'm also so lucky! Because when I finished the Archon Quests yesterday, I thought, "So, no more Archon Quests?? Oh, that's sad. Then I will not have much motivation to keep playing this game." And then on the following day I watch this trailer talking about the next city to visit, the Electro Archon, and "eternity". That's too much of a coincidence and luck too, if they are really going to continue the Archon Quests right after I finished the last one. :)

text:
¬†@Omar¬† 
Yeah i know about albedos quote, but the Original Commentor wrote "seems like Mihoyo already raising a flag on Albedo"
And i just don't see where anything in that specific trailer points towards albedo.
Pretty much any character could die in the future for whatever reasons we might not know yet.
Archons are a huge probability after already losing their gnosis, Albedo, Childe for being involved with the  Mafia + resulting family drama, maybe even sooner the electro archon in her desperate hunt for eternity/immortality.
And if Albedo really thinks he could destroy the whole world and goes berserk, I highly doubt that only he'd die.
Who knows.
I'd just take the quote as a general information to all the people who haven't read ningguangs backstory, and  don't know that visions can fade but also be re-used.
Because from what i get from the trailer:
Electro Archon is taking  back all/as much visions as possible.
Beidou collects faded and not working visions and holds a clash to find people who can reignite the visions again (therefor the information, so we know whatt and why its going on)
Kazuha stole one of these faded visions, and actually reignited it with anemo.

text:
PERSONAL OPINION RIGHT THERE 

man im honestly growing tired of those misc event/update, i just want inazuma or chasm, ill be real this my honest opinion, but when we pass through the schedulde 1.5 chasm 1.6 inazuma it just makes me want to play less, Ar56 and i bet these mini event shown in the trailer will be finished in 3 hours max, i love genshin man but bring out some massive update, the last one which can count as a big update was 1.2 who came with dragonspine,1.3 didnt like it even tho i like xiao why because there is more npc than xiao in the XIAO story quest, it felt like npc pervases story quest. 1.4 did bring with it one of the best quest of all genshin(because its the main story quest) but the mini events were short. 1.5 is where i drew the line, i finished zhongli story quest the day it came out was hyped a lot about azdaha when i first fight him it was all amazing, but thats it, got zhongli on his banner 3 days after he came out but i felt like ive already completed whats important in 1.5 update, the housing is ok, although i didnt like the amount of time you need to wait, why do we even build a house, for what, flexing? i like animal crossing type of game but this felt like a chore to me go farm the tree take your coin, purchase new construction, wait... and repeat, its the same problem its fun the first hours but it gets boring fast, the only update where i didnt felt that feeling was in 1.2 i didnt rush dragonspine and it was fkn amazing the chest reward the little easter egg hidden in the map, only thing i didnt like was how abrupt the albedo story quest finished.

if you read all of this, man i love you

text: ¬†@ferry aldi¬† nah let's be more optimistic here. I'm almost certain it's coming soon, maybe during the 1st year anniversary or a little before then. If you look at 3:11 its showing what looks to be Inazuma islands, they seem to match some of the concept art we've seen already. The one on the left looks like Narukami Island (although it could also be Tsurumi Island) and the one on the far right looks like it has the serpent skull on Yashiori Island. And the one in between them seems to be Seirai Island with the floating rock formation. And we're getting the prologue for Act II in 1.6, which is the Inazuma chapter so the story is already moving forward. Also if you look at the very top left of 2:43, you'll see the icon for Inazuma. There's lots of hints that it's gonna get released soon (maybe not entirely but some of it's locations for sure)

author: Edward Elk

text:
¬†@Di·ªáp Tri·ªáu¬† Story 5
After hundreds of years, Qiqi was discovered by humans, still trapped in amber, and was brought to Wangsheng Funeral Parlor for burial.

The mountain roads were treacherous, however, and the amber was bumped about. Coupled with the passing of many years, the seal on Qiqi was all but spent.

She awakened in the middle of the night, broke the amber in secret, and fled.

Following the herb-picking habits of her previous life, Qiqi headed right for the hills.

By chance, she met Baizhu, the boss of Bubu Pharmacy, on the way, and he took her in.

Now, Baizhu was a doctor of great skill, but he was hardly a man of high caliber or great courage.

Even so, he took her in, nevermind that her memory was so poor that she could not even sort herbs out.

It does seem that his acceptance of Qiqi has something to do with his own personal pursuits.

Qiqi is stiff, but not slow, and has long realized this. However, she does not take it to heart. Perhaps she has seen too much, or been alone for too long... But what remains true is she treasures his concern, even if there is some other motive behind it.
author: Edward Elk

text:
¬†@Edward Elk¬† Dude read story 4. 

The adepti could not bear to let her die, and each imparted to her a portion of their strength, meaning to breathe life back into her body.


Qiqi did indeed awaken and live again, but went into a berserk state, unable to control the adepti energy raging through her.


Seeking to end the disturbance, Mountain Shaper had no choice but to seal the hapless maiden in amber.

(ALL IS THEORY TAKE IT WITH A GRAIN OF SALT)

(This one is confirmed by Lisa, read more) It's possible that visions are devices used by celestia in order to spy the people of Teyvat, Lisa knows that visions are a curse rather than a blessing and knows that one day visions will bring the dark side of themselves (Mona's opinion about Lisa) (More about Lisa: V)

Vision define a superior characteristic of a person.

Pyro - Passion and a possibility of loneliness 

Hydro - Lacking malicious intentions in working and a possible of friendliness

Cryo - Confliction of ones innerself and possible of persistence

Electro - Special people and independence as a possible secondary trait

Anemo - People of dedication and inner stress and sadness as a possibilty 

Geo - Hardworking people and a possiblity to be stubborn

Dendro - Unknown, we don't have enough characters to know the pattern of personalities

text:
¬†@S. T¬† Correct!  And the people (other than the archons and maybe, maybe, the adepti   are unreliable narrators.  They are telling the traveler what they have been told/believe not necessarily what is.)   What the meteor event revealed was visions are Celestia's way of watching people.
Zhongli: "Visions...  are also a type of contract. You should know that all power comes at a price. For every bit of power you gain, so too do you gain more responsibility."    [hesitancy, caution, and avoidance subtext]
Venti: [does not speak on their origin]
Traveler: [none on visions atm, which is interesting in that regard]

My guess is that either an archon or celestia can directly grant a vision. That most vision bearers have been selected by celestia [most visions just appear next to a person, and archons are not omnipresent].  Celestia may teleport the vision to them, or have the local archon deliver in person.  The element is based upon the individuals character and which archon they are most similar to in that regard.  The archon can stop the element from appearing in new visions all over teyvat, but cannot stop visions of other elements from appearing in their own territory. 


Bonus:  Seelie
Traveler: "..why do I feel a certain sadness...'  "...probably just my imagination..."
Dainslef:  "she too loved these flowers"
Hokai Impact: Seelie [person] has strong connection [representation] with flower and also butterfly
Guess: Seelie a non ruling (non-gnosis) archon was killed during the destruction of khan. Perhaps she was helping the people there. Celestia forced the ruling archons to attack by invoking 'authority' with the gnosis. Controlled Barbatos was the one that killed her, hence Tsaritsa (most likely based off of Bronya) anger at venti, and even more so at celestia.

text:
¬†@Ponto √Çncora Marketing Digital¬† It isn't, or at least it hasn't been confirmed. Keqing thanks Morax for her vision and Klee does the same with Barbatos. Zhongli didn't know that visions allow users to wield elemental power. Xiao's story refers to visions as "recognitions from Celestia" which is a different thing from the archons. And now that we're speaking about Xiao, he got his "vision" before The Seven were even a thing.

Not to mention how unlikely it is that the Cryo Archon is just giving her visions away to people like Diona, on an entire different region, while simultaneously preparing for a war against said nations AND not giving visions to her own Fatuis.

text:
Notice that, in this case as the narrator says "when a vision bearer dies, the light in their vision fades away" we see an Inazuma vision with no power in it, which means that, most likely, the character to reveal this part of existence to us will be one from Inazuma. Right after, Beidou says that she's hoping for a vision to glow again in this tournament and if we go by the story of how Ningguang got her vision, it means that they can attune themselves to new people as long as the previous bearer is alive (keeping the abandoned vision active).

In my opinion, this probably means that Beidou is aware of this rule of visions and is willing to test it on an inactive one she was either given, found or something else. Her tone also gives the impression that she's tried this before but it didn't work and this is merely another attempt. Kazuha's participation might mean, then, that he either knew the deceased person and is hoping to get the vision back or is generally interested in this rule. We also can't forget that the traveler is making a reputation as well, which means he might also be coming into contact out of curiosity.

Anyway, this is my theory for the moment. I am very concerned with the vision phrase.

author: le marionette shad

text:
It is specifically stated that the previous owner of Ningguang's vision is deceased, the visions stop completely working after the owners passes away but they can resonate with someone else after that and only after that. That's how Ningguang got hers, the owner died, and it resonated with her. They don't just "abandon" visions, the owner must die for a slight chance of someone else using it.

As for the rest of your theory yes, I agree. It seems like this will be an illegal tournament of sorts, and the big prize is a deactivated vision. So Kazuha might as well know the previous owner and wants it back, or Beidou sent him to win and test it themselves.

text: Despite what everyone is saying about death flags about empty visions in trying to think about what this could mean for Beidou and Kazuha. Beidou is holding a contest specifically so someone can receive a vision, which is an event that will likely draw a lot of Inazumans to try and compete considering the fact that Baal  (the electro archon) isn‚Äôt handing out visions anymore and confiscating them from anyone who does, this could be their only chance to receive a vision. (This is going off the assumption that the archons give out visions in their area of worship and not the ones that correlate to their respective element.)  I imagine we will have a side quest of portion of the main story dedicated to tracking down the missing vision and finding Kazuha as its new bearer, which I believe he either stole (least likely in my opinion), resonated with and took with him unknowing about the tournament, or resonated with during battle. We could also have a random person steal it or just pick it up without knowing what it actually is (considering the one shown on screen isn‚Äôt resonated with any element and just looks like a fancy glass ball) and in an attempt to get it back it will end up resonating with Kazuha.

text:
¬†@GuilesTheme¬† Yes, I am complaining because instead of them wasting their resources on making events, they could use that time to re-write the story they want to fix and possibly give us small updates as it comes. I'm okay with not having these updates and events if it means the actual story will be finished. I'm showing passion because I do care for this game and like others, want to see this games conclusion. 

"Give it time" it's been almost 2 years since this games announcement and you mean to tell me Inazuma will barely come out this year? At this pace at one nation a year?  The game will die at that pace and I don't want it to. 

I would believe they are working their asses off, once more of the story is out. These events are not a requirement. Maybe something on the side they can do, but not use full updates for and use it to pass time to rewrite the story. 

So how much time would I have to give them really? More than a year? People are gonma lose interest if the story is not out.
author: NeptuneTheDothacker

text:
¬†@GuilesTheme¬† And honestly, if they didn't want this kind of feedback, they should've held off on releasing Genshin to console by another year or two. A lot of console players expect complete games by the time it releases and I'm sure PC and mobile gamers would want the same thing once it's released multi-platform.

Actually here's a novel idea. If people want them to take their time with the story, cool fine let them. Story needs to be great and take it's time I'm cool with it. 

But instead of them relasesing some stupid event every 6 weeks, maybe they can expand the world every 6 weeks and polish what needs to be polished and take their time with the story. At least it'll give us something to work with instead of these events.

text: I don't know. People really seem to love the "new gameplay" in every event, but I honestly feel it's a bit wasted. Not only is the game not made for all these things (like Windtrace) and they are therefore just implmented but barely optimized, but they get deleted after the event anyway. I would really love to explore again which is the main draw of the game for me and I assume a lot of others too, which seems is at least possible, but I doubt that the area is even close to at least Dragonspine. It's been over six months since the last new area and since the start of the game, there was no major new region. I want to be astonished again, not just busy, because there is an event. Also, am I the only one that thinks the beach skins look boring in their design? Normal design of Jean and Barbara looks way better. But I guess I don't need to use them.

text:
¬†@Ailura Shia¬† Barbatos and Morax do not use Visions because they don't need them. Before even becoming an Archon they were still gods and had great control over a certain element (Geo and Anemo). They are still immortal and still Gods even though they no longer have their gnoses. A Gnosis is essentially a divine item that allows the Archons to directly tap into Celestial power from Celestia directly through them, and also they symbolise their status as Archons.
Do not forget that Morax, before becoming an Archon, fought and slaughtered many other gods, slaying them and then pinning them underground with gigantic geo lances, and Barbatos I believe, if I'm not mistaken, that was also quite the force to be reckoned with. I do know that Barbatos even terraformed the land of Mondstadt, ridding it of the impossible mountains, clearing the ocean and purifying the air... So on and so forth, he basically SHAPED Mondstadt.

So yeah, they don't use Visions and the one they carry are fakes to avoid suspicion.

I've been waiting for this :3
So I got a little theory about the supposed criteria for visions:
Pyro : passionate people that will do anything for the things they love
Cryo : people that endlessly fights against something either physically, mentally or emotionally
Hydro : i think those that have huge amount of love for something or someone
Geo : Dutiful people that will accomplish their responsibilities no matter what
Anemo : basically people that love and understand freedom
Electro : the skeptic of the world and those that goes against the general society or common sense
Dendro : what dendro? Jk but i think wise people would make the most sense but let's just see

P.S : Some of this you really need to analyze a character deeper but i think All of the character at least embody a part of this criteria in their backstory or personality

text:
¬†@Ash¬†Edit: Read the edit below for correction. I don't wanted give off as if I was hiding my mistake so I left the original part of comment as it is

 I don't think Archons grants visions. All the game told us so far is that "gods" grants visions it could be the gods of celestia for all we know.
*SPOILER WARNING for new players*
And the reason why I think visions aren't granted by archons it's cause we know the role of archon was granted for the victors of archon war and Zhongli story quest act 1 we know that Rex lapis used the power of geo against Osial to hurl giant rock spears against him, or when he unearthed Azhdaha using some geo power. And that was all before he was an archon. He also fought Chi dragon at some point and used the power of geo to pin down his body after defeating him.
Venti also said at the end of Act Prologue that even the archons possess visions but unlike normal visions which are external foci, the one gods possess are internal foci.

Edit: So I came back to my this comment (after getting a certain quest in game) to correct some of the above stuff.
(1). The quest confirmed that Archons gives out the visions to people
(2). The trailer kinda confirms that we'll be getting that empty vision and that will be our electro element. Cause Beidou in the trailer says that she's holding the competition (this time) to see if the vision could glow again. We also know from Ningguang story that she also got her vision from an empty vision. So maybe it really does work like green lantern rings?
author: Latifa Fleuranza

¬†@Ash¬† And as for borrowing powers from statue, we know from Act IV part II that those are from Celestia. There's also visual similarities between the skyfrost nail in dragonspine and these statues and **cough**... **cough**.. a certain traveling companion.

author: Josh Brosh

text:
¬†@Koong SH¬† free? lol every single thing in the game is locked behind some kind of gambling. be that artifacts rolling or content.

dont get me wrong, i like the game, i agree that it looks amazing, but the monetization is just disgusting. 

how come i pay ~15$ a month and am still not allowed to meaningfully use the content i have unlocked, some of which also with payment, because anything meaningfull is gated by resin. yes, you can play this game for free, but people who actually realy get into it pay with their soul because they miss out on about 90% of the content they would at least like to have just a basic unlock for.

do you realize that a 100$ purchase in the game essentially gives you an about 26% (50 wishes) chance to actually get a 5star character?
granted, if you spend 200$ a 5star is guaranteed!
oh whats that? there is only a guarantee of getting the character in the banner every other roll if you didnt get it previously?

if you are INSANELY lucky, and noone should ever expect that to happen, you need
700$
thats sevenhundred
dollars
to get a SINGLE 5star to c6

Realisticly speaking, that gets you to c3, c4 at best.

im just gonna leave my survey text here and i would encourage anyone to just copypaste or put something similar. theres things about this game that need to change before im going to consider praising it over all:



The existance of Resin for players that already pay for your "game as a service" is an absolute joke. There is no justification for it and its just obvious and pure greed. It is honestly disgusting and everytime i think about it i get more and more upset about it. you just dont care about your customers, that much is obvious, and are only taking every single opportunity to milk more money off of them. im honestly suprised that there is actually a cap on how much more expensive the resin purchases get.
Im getting the blessing and the battlepass everytime. Thats effectively a subscription, and youre still gating me from doing anything meaningfull in the game by locking everything behind resin, and then even implimenting systems that are designed to drain your resin as much as possible and giving you literal trash for it (more on that in the next paragraph). 

The artifact system is one of the worst things ive ever seen in any game ever. I grinded for nothing else for the past 1-2 weeks. i, in total, got 3 artifacts that have more then 2 usable substats for any given character, and every single one of them  (allong side every other artifact that had at least 2 usable stubstats) got either DEF, DEF%, HP or HP%. on at least 2 of the 3 substatups i gave them. I am forced to upgrade horrible artifacts, because within 1000 artifacts that are stored in my inventory at a time, there is maybe 5 that are actually good and those already are on 20. let that sink in.
there is no more then two characters in the game that i dont actually cringe if i have to put defense on them, but even on those, almost every single other stat is probably still better. NOONE EVER wants defense Artifacts, yet they are by far the most common ones (sharing the #1 spot with health). That entire stat can be just flatout removed and the handfull of defense scalings that are in the game can just be changed to health.
This system needs to be changed, its just terrible. give us the option to chose which substats to upgrade. that way artifacts that dont start out with 4 stats arent flatout worse either, they would be simply more felxible initialy for a slight tradeoff in maximal power.


Your prices otherwhise, are absolutely insane. Im gonna be VEEEERY generous and well just say you get a 5 star character every 50 rolls, even tho theres only an about 26% chance of that happening. that is still
100$
for ONE 5star
so it is, at LEAST 700$ to get one on C6.
and at worst 1400$, if you only get it every other time.
AND THAT is the the MOST GENEROUS estimation one could make. you can pretty much double those numbers and it would still be a fair assumption of the price. how can anyone look at this and go "yup this is fine".

same for the weapon banner but its even worse here. i still want my staff of homa. i got 3 gravestones and then gave up because a forth one would have been just useless and i already had the lithic spear on max ref at that point, so i gues im never getting a homa unless i spend literal thousands of dollars the next time it comes arround.
let people chose which of the 5stars they want.

another thing: the compensation you get for rolling something you already heave on full constellation is an absolute joke. i was terrefied of roling for Eula because i realy wanted her, but i could only get 1 more constellation for any of the 4stars on the banner and didnt have a guarantee for her. if i was reasonably compensated for duplicates i would have maybe considdered rolling more on her and getting her in the first place would have been a less agonizing experiance, but like this im just happy i didnt waste too many wishes.
25 starglitter would be a fairer compensation then 5. the odds you get another 4 star in those are not great (about 23%) if you chose to get wishes for it, but its possible, and it moves you closer to pitty. you also can just get a 4star weapon from paimons bargains for that.


You, as a company, blatantly spit in my, the customers, face. with everything ive brought up so far. this is how i genuenly feel about this, and i will certainly not recommend the game to anyone else, lest they fall for the things youre doing right:

Core Gameplay and Design.
The game is fun. It genuenly is. you just don't let me play it (refere to paragraph 1).
There is things i would like to see tweaked (critrate/damage scalings and the way elemental mastery works), but the foundation is solid. The only thing that genuenly annoys me is autotargeting. a toggle for on/off/on ranged only/on melee only, would be aprechiated here.

It also looks amazing.
There is A LOT of potential here, give us raid bosses with proper mechanics, give us skins, and don't do like you did with honkai, i assure you, everyone loves bunnygirls.


in conclusion: RNG is inherently not fun. Gambling is not fun. Only the success is. noones happy about losing a 50/50. Progression is fun, but you lock every bit of that behind heaving to gambe with terrible odds stacked against you and insane prices you charge for it. therefore you're no better then a greedy casino in Las Vegas with a fancy architecture and a pretty fountain outside, that prays on its customers by exploiting those lacking self control. Nice to look at, but horrible and disgusting in principle.

author: Vicky Zhang

text:
¬†@Elder Roll¬† 
Warframe is a free game, and it looks and plays like a AAA yet it still gets criticism. So should Genshin, it looks like a AAA but the gameplay itself is boring, after you finish all your quests, you're free to roam a desert wasteland of nothing. Reused maps, Reused weapon models (Prototype and Archaic, Compound Bow and Windblume Ode, this is honestly minor, but still should be brought to contrast all the constant praise Mihoyo keep getting), badly made event gadgets, flawed event (Lantern Rite fetch quests). The only thing you do now is login, do daily commission, swallow all your resin, and do the small events. At least the events are getting better, but back then it was so boring, "Geovishap and where to find them," is just a copy paste from the expedition screen. Plus, this game have made 1B alone in 6 months, so using "it's a free game," is no excuse when they have so much resource to make it bigger. The only limitation is the game being on mobile, which I honestly think they should pull the plug on that. The game already over 20GB, times 5 more continent and you're gonna need more than your average phone. That's not mentioning new enemy, and the story content.

The big 3 problems of Genshin being:
-Hacker (fixed but took 6 months for that.)
-Resin system
-Endgame content 

Resin system and endgame content is a two bird one stone situation, but god are they taking long. A lot of my friend had already left, and I decided to stay and wait Incase it did get worthwhile, the last 1.3, and 1.5 was honestly pretty painful. But I'm still waiting for this game to be worthwhile for something to invest money to outside of gambling for a shortlived 2 seconds of excitement of getting a character I won't build. This gives up hope, but everyone said that about the housing system as well, so I won't hold my breath.

author: Millena Brezier

text:
¬†@Elder Roll¬† 
The difference between Genshin and other online game is online game only gets boring because of the grind. Even then, other online games can give you enough time, experience and memorable moments, not to mentioned finished story for them to be worth the money. Genshin gets boring because there's nothing to do, the resin system is very limiting for you to grind and even after you get a perfect artifact you can only use them for one thing and that is the spiral abyss. After you beat that you just uninstall the game. The only latest good content I've considered they've given us is 1.2 Dragonspine and everything else after that is extremely dissapointing. 1.3 gave us probably the worst fetch quest festival I've ever seen, not to mention a dissapointing 1B primogem distribution event that was unfair to all players. 1.4 finally gave us a good festival that was tainted by how poorly made the lyre and the free weapon Windbloom Ode is. And 1.5 just gave us Sims 4 + Cookie Clicker without the Sims nor the clicker. Just saying "good content will come," isn't good enough. People need to be critical about the flaws of the game. Like the hacker issue for example, a problem prevalence from day 1 fixable by simply implementing a 2FA system which they already have on their other IP and account security. Yet it took them 6 months, half a year long for them to do anything about it. Had people be more critical of this problem and actually criticizing Mihoyo for this, we'd probably get it far quicker, yet the community remain silent.

author: Elder Roll

text:
‚Äã¬†@Elder Roll¬† 
God. I thought I was gonna find a rational enough person to actually see and criticise the flaw of the game rather than be a white knight and defend it at every corner. So much for hope. The community biggest problem of white knighting basic problems that should have been handled by Mihoyo... Where do I even begin?

"I suggest you to stop."
Great work at telling Mihoyo's customer to shoo off. I like this game, I like the artstyle, the characters, the story, but by no mean is this a GAME it might as well be a movie and that honestly would have been better in my opinion. What's wrong with you white knights? You know you can criticise something that you like, right? I don't mind if you like it, that's subjective, but from an objective point of view, tell me what did you do last time to have fun? The 5 things I've mentioned, Login, Dailies, Resin, Event, Logout, and nothing else... Rivetting gameplay right there... My friends already left and I told them I'd wait for the game to be worth it and notify them, yet after 3 big updates it still barely changed... if Mihoyo think "To the stars Once more," web event is gonna get any players back they'd be dead wrong. Tell me, from Dragonspine 1.2 to Serenitea Pot 1.5, what have ACTUALLY changed rather than pointless filler and quality of life changes that should have been here much earlier... And you'd expect them to improve on them without any critcism? Where do you think anyone's improvement ever come from?

"Wait 1-2years,"
Wow, let the game starve of revenue and player numbers just for them to actually get their act together and care! That's like saying an anime would get good after 10 seasons of filler. I don't play video games for them to "get good in a decade," I play video games to have fun NOW. Not, "waiting in line simulator," or "it gets better soon simulator." God almighty, are you hearing yourself? "Just don't play in 3 years," mate, if I didn't play that long, I won't even dare visit this game again. I'd just actually have fun on other games. I'm being patient and waiting, even after 3 whole dissapointment, and the community non-stop white knighting of this games flaws. But once I speak about something that displease me, its instantly "whining?" Screw off...

"this game's main story contents are not finish."
Warframe main story contents aren't finished, yet it still have more content, same goes with Honkai, Arknight, etc. I'm sick of tired of "its not a finished game," excuse. So what, you're telling me they shouldn't release this game in the first place? Sure sounds like you are saying that... You're saying this game quality should be comparable to horrible early access releases on steam? When a game release, it should have CONTENT not "waiting simulator 2020." And don't get me started on the "It's a free game," excuse.
-CS:GO
-Apex Legends
-Destiny 2
-Path of Exile
-Smite
-Paladins
-Star Trek Online
-Runescape
-Eve Online
-Planetside 2
-Brawlhalla
-Heroes of the Storm
-Team Fortress 2
-Warframe
-Endless array of other free mobile games.

I don't see you or others defending these game with the BS "its a free game," excuse, and Mihoyo even made 1 Billion dollars in 6 MONTHS, game that sit their whole shelf life can't even get that much money in that time! And the thing they gave us with that amount of revenue is a Sims 4 Furnishing Idle game? Think about that for a second... Free games are used to show how the game has limits in what content it could put out based on the revenue they're making, and Mihoyo has shown they have no problem in that department, so where's the content from earlier that I talked about, what have changed since 1.2?

"plus the game has regular surveys. use it to express your comments/suggestions."
I did, the same thing I'm writing here, and what did I see when I look at the developer discussion? "Oh, you want alchemy table to be usable in Co-op UwU," like WOW! Amazing feedback devs... What a joke. I'm sorry you're persoanlly hurt that your game is being critized for whatever reason, but gosh, they have been soo many setback and wasted potential that the community is just gonna turn a blind eye on cause they're a white knight fanboys. People have talked about wanting a shield meter for months, no progress on that, 2FA and better security since day one, took them 6 months, and end game content from day 1 which we see no progress being made on until this trailer... And even then, this would likely be another bygone event. I'm sorry you see criticism as "hate," since people who actually criticise stuff actually care for the stuff they're criticizing, how do you think ANYONE improves? By getting yesmen to validate all their horrible actions and decision? What a joke...

"Use better pw/I dunno other game which uses 2FA"
God, do you know how people got hacked? Massive information leak from Mihoyo own database, that's why 2FA was necessaery, since Mihoyo themself can't stop leaking account information of other players! No amount of password is gonna save you from hackers copy pasting your account info to the login screen. Of course not, you're a white knight ignorant of the company's flaws... That's why 2FA was necessary, it isn't an additional useless addon, it was detremental to most people account safety! And that's because Mihoyo own security is horrible, why do you think character and version leaks keep coming out?! 

But sure, I'll stop, and then 100k follow suite, then 200k more, then 500k more, how about 1M? How about 1.5M? I guess that's your viewpoint on this game huh? Genshin is for "special," people like you who doesn't have enough cognitive ability to actually criticise it. Wowee... If the game doesn't get anything worthwhile anymore the only people who will be playing is people who've been deep in sunk cost fallacy or white knight like you who sees falling player number as a "good thing," Mihoyo is aware this game is losing player numbers, what do you think "To the Stars once more," web event was for? Before then, all Ads from Mihoyo I've seen was for Honkai, even after Genshin have reach half a year old. They only now have started actually making and releasing Ads for Genshin, because Genshin is losing players and popularity, people are fed up with the treatment they've been giving us and I can't blame them. But go on, talk about how "its a free game," or "the story isn't finished," like thats a valid way to rationalize this games shortcoming, don't come crying back for players to come back for your totally generous 500 primo web event.

Genshin pales in comparison to other games. The only thing people talk about this game is how pretty it looks, the character, and the story. Notice how gameplay is the least thing talked about in this game unless you're a minmaxer. For a game, that is honestly pathetic. Tell me again, if the gameplay is so great, what do you do in the game? Login, Dailies, Resin, Event, Logout. Oh, sorry I forgot the housing, the "wait until a currency is filled," system. Rivetting gameplay. Compare that to Warframe where you have 3 open world, multiple mission types, different characters, multiple modifications, tons of weapon choice, bounties, space ship battles, etc. God almighty, stop being a white knight and actually listen to reason. I don't say you have to agree, but at least try to understand where people are coming from rather than instantly taking any complaints as "whining."
Geez.
author: Spooky Scary Lamppost

text: and the fact that its not required to pay anything aswell
author: McGanyu

text: ¬†@Spooky Scary Lamppost¬† i would like to say something minor, the hacking situation never existed. There was never a data breech at mihoyo's end. It was, to be put simply, the consumer's fault. Of course there are the scams, but people have a week password for their email, weak  and reused genshin login, and buying accounts. Mihoyo was in the right and 2fa isn't even used in many games anymore. Mihoyo listened despite completely knowing they were right and still added 2fa. Those who would've been hacked before will still be hacked now because of their inability to make a good password. 2fa can still be bypassed if there was a data breech. Also, a side note: mihoyo being a Chinese company, has no access to Google. They can't just ctrl+c ctrl+v Google's 2fa in their game. They had to build it from the ground up to make sure no ones info will get leaked while using their 2fa. They work hard to make their players happy. Although I can't justify many mistakes that a small indie company makes, I believe that their game will be astonishing. If the new areas will be the size of liyue or mondstadt, I wonder what kind of game it will become.
author: ItsJustJeff

text:
¬†@ItsJustJeff¬† 
From the bottom of my heart, THANK YOU, for being a person that can give me actual and new perspective about the whole situation rather than some white knight who gives the same BS excuses. Although I still do have some question myself if you do have any further info on this:


-Even though Mihoyo can't use Google own 2FA, they still have had them on their previous IP Honkai, and even as something needed to change account details. If so, is it really hard to replicate it for Genshin even though they've had done it before?
-I find it hard that its purely the consumer fault, as there's been A LOT of victim of these hacking. 

From rebelsimpact: " now as I can see on the telegram GI hacking group, everyday they have been getting 5K - 10K accounts and sold them to the public" 

Which is a lot. Of course, this is a bit subjective, but I find it hard that only the consumer is to be blamed here, especially 5-10k of them. Not to mention famous users ike Enviosity, Mtashed and Tectone who were also victims. I know they're famous, thus they're a stuck out like a sore thumb, but I find it hard that they've used shady websites or weak passwords. Again though, this is purely speculation on my ends.

Other than that, I wouldn't really call Mihoyo a "small indie company." They have 2400 employees, compare to Valve a AAA that have around 360 employees. Not to mention their office being in Shanghain the most expensive place to set up your HQ in China. I'm hoping for this game to have a good future, but god is it hard with the constant onslaught of white knighting from this community.

author: Di·ªáp Tri·ªáu

text:
¬†@Di·ªáp Tri·ªáu¬† I would like to say, "No, I still believe that whoever finds their own meaning in said item can cherish it as much as they like, no matter who bashes you." As much as there are believers in the Japanese meaning for the Maple Leaf, I know there are several individuals that claim to choose the Chinese meaning of the Maple Leaf. I respect their choices and yours too. 

I learned what I knew from a close Chinese family six or seven years ago, and I caught wind of this comment, and to share a bit of that introspective knowledge, I also want to say I respect the Japanese meaning as well, as that is the most popular chosen meaning.  Others can have their own meaning to it, even if it doesn't come from their namesake.

I can give a tiny example of what I mean if you'd like.
author: Blu [TB34]

text:
¬†@Blu [TB34]¬† The point here is that kazuha is a japanese base character. So it's extremely disrespectful to not take it as japanese ideal. The devs of the game spend a lots of time research other country's culture. So if we go with what the dev mean, it's definitely a referance to japanese culture as a whole

I don't think you can talk much about chinese or japanese culture when you only know 1 chinese family. My country also have extremely close tie to chinese culture. Yet, i don't claim to know the culture more than the surface.

author: buluhterbang

text: ¬†@Wolfhooks¬† Alice travel A LOT, just like Traveller. Remember KFC Genshin Wing? Remember Barbara's idol magazine brought by her? And few in-game lore here and there mentioning how many different worlds she travelled, not just Tevyat. That old musical instrument might be something she brought with her and the way she sound is just how Alice is - crazy loving mom who'll do anything to keep her daughter prepared for the world's danger/remember her/not missing her mom too much.
author: buluhterbang

text: ¬†@Ray¬† the string is probably just aesthetic related to Japanese string puppet culture and we have to wait until the update as to what Alice meant in her message. Knowing how crazy she is and all the bombs she taught her daughter to make, I believe she trust her daughter that she can handle any danger there is on the island. Also, she trust Jean with her, probably that's why she's confident to let her child believe in Dodoco and the evil stuff too. Can't wait how this will turn out later in the update!
author: buluhterbang

text: ¬†@buluhterbang¬† BRUHHHH You think Alice really went beyond Tevyat?!? Cause their are several theories that say that the world of Genshin is connected to the modern world of Honkai. Theory: Kazuha HAD a vision from Inazuma, when he was exiled he got another vision from the battle thingy that beidou holds

Edit: Considering that anemo vision is actually from Inazuma, it could mean 2 things:

1: Kazuha started with an Anemo vision, nothing else (Still confused with his design tho)

2: The vision came from a dead vision bearer from Inazuma, and was maybe in posession by Beidou, which might be connected with the whole battle arena thing and Kazuha joining the Crux, if this was the case he maybe had a Pyro Vision when he was in Inazuma, and was stripped off it when he was exiled, after which he met the crux through that arena, and ended up making an Anemo vision glow again which he then made it his own vision, and now officially part of the crux.

As for why he got an anemo vision, maybe previously he was passionate about whatever job he did for Inazuma but changed views when the electro archon started locking down inazuma, he started to have an ideal in maybe making Inazuma free again and figure out why the electro archon did it in the first place through his own way.

But then again i could be completely overcomplicating this lmao

author: QRIUSMEERKAT

text: it's common for English dub of East Asian language, since Chinese and Japanese are both a lot more syllable efficient (same amount of sound conveys more meaning than in English), the English VA needs more time to cover the same info. When there's a music/pv/game going on and you can't adjust the pacing for EN, the result is usually something like this. A good example is from Fist of North Star: Lost Paradise. It's a game about a fighting manga where characters shout their moves when making them. One boss fight between MC and a guy named Rei sees the guy shouting a move that's about 10 syllable in Japanese, and you can hear the EN va doing a mini rap to cover the same name in English.

text:
While the game have its flaws, I agree, the updates are pretty good.
1.1 basically wraps the first chapter, and while it's relatively light in content compared to later updates, still pretty decent.
1.2 was basically an expansion pack with 1 new region, and while my feelings on Dragonspine were mixed, overall it's pretty good, the only thing i didn't like are the sheer cold system, the rest are good especially the soundtrack.
1.3 was a mixed bag, sure the events gave us so many rewards, and the tower defense was pretty fun, but the lantern quests was repetitive as hell, and the main story is kinda meh imo. Still pretty fun, especially if you're f2p.
1.4 was 1.3 but better, the festival's main story is pretty good, and the minigames were fun too. And, they teased us with many lore revelations too. Oh and yeah, the hangout stories are an excellent addition too.
1.5 introduces a housing system, and many amazing side content; a new boss, 2 new story quest, and some of the best minigame in the game.
